            <div type="glosses">
                <note xml:id="CASTELALTOGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">Missing name 
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVIII">MS VIII</title>)&#x2014;</hi>Evidently 
                    undecided about a name for the castle, Ruskin left a gap for the name to be filled later. 
                    His eventual decision, as printed in Friendship's Offering, 
                    was <placeName type="fictional" corresp="#CASTELALTO-LEONI"><hi rend="italic">Castel Alto</hi></placeName>.</p></note>

                <note xml:id="OLDMANGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;the old man&#x201D; 
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVIII">MS VIII</title>)&#x2014;</hi>In the final text 
                    for Friendship's Offering, Ruskin replaced "the old man" with the name he had since settled, 
                    Amalfiero.</p></note>
                
                <note xml:id="GARCIOGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;brother; Garcio was feared&#x201D; 
                    (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVIII">MS VIII</title>)&#x2014;</hi>The wide gaps on either side of the name Garcio 
                    perhaps indicates that here, like the gap left at the beginning of the story to be filled in with the name of the old man, 
                    Ruskin had temporized over the name of Giulietta's brother, as well</p></note>
            </div>
